title.narrative: SUPPORT TO CO ON EMERG PREP AND RESPONSE

description.narrative: UNICEF Country Offices receive effective, timely and coordinated support in preparing for and responding to humanitarian crises, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: GRP2 2016-17: MENA Country Offices and the RO are empowered to deliver timely, equitable and principled humanitarian action, including through the cross-border component of the Syria programmes as part of the Whole of Syria response.
